cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper focuses on the development of a text processing platform that utilizes Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques for semantic analysis of web content. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and linguistic analysis. The paper also discusses information retrieval (IR) and information extraction (IE), which are relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of statistical distribution and machine learning techniques for indexing and weighting semantic units is also relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and the discussion of domain-specific search engines is relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
